# Target Dependent Assembly

The varied syntax of target assembly along with their semantics calls for 
a progromatic approach to definition of their intermediate representation.
To ease the development of a new target for the compiler. 

we could attempt to define a set of structures which are abstract enough that they
encapsulate all possible forms of assembly, and generate against that.

we could attempt to define an API against which we generate and which particular form 
becomes a small addition to the existing code generator.

or something else. 

I think, since our chosen language is Zig, we will want to utilize the compile time code 
evaluation facilities, which are used to define abstract types, to define abstract 
assembly types. and these forms are used to construct the API.

This structure is dependent on the shape of the code generator however, so we might 
wait to attempt a definition until we have written that.

